    "Told In Brief World Oil Pool Plan Fails New York Juie 2Representatives of all the biggest oil interests in the world meeting for the past several days in the Hotel Waldorf Astoria announced yesterday that the plan to divide the world markets had failed Attempts of the De terding and Standard Oil groups to force the So viet Union to give them a monopoly in the Near East which now buys U S S R oil are thought to have been responsible Miners Defeat National Guardsmen Nelsonville Ohio June 2 Two hundred and forty national guardsmen that Governor White sent in to break the strike were defeated by the militant spirit of the coal miners One hundred guardsmen are guarding 20 scabs five guards men to one scab in the Lick Run mine and in spite of the terror of the troops who fired 40 shots at the strike pickets on Monday night the miners are having mass militant picketing pre venting any more scabs from entering the mine tJ Federal Deficit Now 2684950500 The deficit in the federal budget for the first eleven months of the fiscal year ending June 30 amounted to 2684950445 on May 31 as compared"
